THE BATTLE CLERIC! 

Prolog 

"the battle cleric is a very controversial figure in the world of everquest, sometimes, to such an extent that their motives are questioned and others flat out refuse to pvp with them, thus i believe it is my duty to enlighten those that have not yet come to understand the full glory of THE BATTLE CLERIC what he truly is and how that benefits others" 

those clerics that practice the fine arts of melee against a target are generally given the term "battle cleric". mainly attributing to there higher then normal AC, ATK, meleeing skills, equipment choices, as well as their extremely aggressive play style. 

battle clerics many times find themselves engaged in roles traditionally reserved for melees proper for pve, such as pulling, and even tanking. 

for pvp, the battle cleric's moniker is his BASH as well as geting some unresistable damage on there target. in Addison to performing there normal clerical duties. 

the battle clerics spits in the face of the tradition, that clerics are lowly heal bitchs thats only job is to read health and mana bars and squeal like stuck pigs if a, mob or player, attacks them. 


(forms of damage and spell line up) 

when mana and circumstance permit clerics are have the ability of doing damage to there targets. 

this takes the form of DD, stun dd, and other "pet"/ cleric melee 

at lvl 54 clerics can use a 5.5 sec 250 mana 7.5 sec repop DD that "possibly best case scenario does about 630 damage to a target that has been tashed PvE" 

for stuns the damage is insignificant and there main purpose is used to interrupt spells so they will not be discussed in depth 

"the pet" is a interesting beast. it only takes 2.5 seconds to cast for 175mana. it has very low hitpoints 100hp, yet it completely magic resistant fire/cold/magic maybe poison and dease too. it also is a very decent dammage dealer in its own right, double attacking for 30s or 70s .. 60-140 dammage per wave of swings. it also adds as anouther "thing" to "deal with" 

and of course the bread and butter of the battle cleric, his own personal melee. at 54 a battle cleric should have 175 1hb skill and 141 bash a delvled 55 cleric has 145 bash skill. 
with an hammer of dubious quality he can swing for 20-30 damage a hit at a rate of 20 dly + whatever haste equitment/spells + a extra weapon proc and bash for 30-70 damage. the bash also creates a stun effect and instantly interrupts its target during casting. 


Of course the spell line up on a battle cleric is METT dependant. but his 6 modular type spells are 

Stuns "stuncommand (55), stun, sounding force, etc) 
heavy heal (divine light, dot heal,CH) 
pet 
DD "reckoning" 
blind (although almost never droped from the spell line up) 
or other (dispell, cures, utility, buffs ect) 

2 divine auras, gate, and quick heal, are always loaded. 

(come on lucky 7) 

when a cleric DDs manytimes this is looked at as rolling the dice, 5.5 seconds of hand giggling required, sence MR is the number 1 most pushed resist in the game, and clerics DD is checked by that resist. it is not a reliable means of dishing out damage. 

Meleeing on the other hand is also an option because you are always going to "get some" and the "bash" is a way to help "control" the target., how many times have you seen a SK or a paladin opt for a 1h weapon so they can BASH? a battle cleric is bringing that to the table also. 

furthermore meleeing can be "turned off" instantly unlike a spell, that requires "ducking" furthermore the damage is done instantly so it isnt "wasted time" unlike a DD, that needed to be stopped because something "more important" came up, such as a reblinding, a stun, or a heal. 

although meleeing is free mana wise it takes is own toll, "target fixation" and losing situational awareness is a constant thorn in there side, yet one they try to over come with experience. 


(battle clerics love attention) 
all clerics know, folks love to kill them, battle clerics tellem to bring it on! 

with high ac and hopefully hitpoints as well as a keen finger on the DA, a battle cleric can easily keep the enemy distracted and keep the enemy from "agrooing" on weaker classes such as wizards and enchanters. also staying near the target and near there teammates without having to "run around like a chickin with there head chopped off" is a good thing because the enchanter will "eventually", get them off you, why make his job even harder? 

and if your there welcoming their blows then why would they run, maybe they can "drag the cleric down with them" hehe unlikely , but the enemy dont know that  

(battle clerics know) 
battle clerics know that they are different, and defy the norm in EQ. because they experiment and try to push the envelope trying to bring out there class's full potential, this is a good thing, yet like all new ways will have some bumps on the noggin geting perfected. also more pressure is put on them because they "have something to prove" so a higher level of performance is demanded out of them, and its to be expected, they are blazing new trails afterall. 


i could run numbers and examples with you all day, but the truth of the matter is, different people play differently. the battle cleric, is a good style of play for a certain type of person thats comfortable with that. for those of you that already have clerics, maybe its something you could try out, you might find it useful yourself, or atleast find new holes in battle clerics play style. either way you will become more informed about your class and i'm sure a better player for it. 

thanks for reading, 
